{{Infobox military person |name=Helmut Kalbitz |birth_date=3 January 1912 |death_date={{death-date and age|23 August 1944|3 January 1912|df=yes}} |birth_place=[[Harburg-Wilhelmsburg]] |death_place=[[missing in action|MIA]] near [[Iași]], Romania |image= |caption= |nickname= |allegiance={{flag|Nazi Germany}} |branch=[[German Army (Wehrmacht)|Heer]] |serviceyears=1935–44 |rank= [[Major (Germany)|Major]] |commands=Pionier-Battalion 31 |unit= |battles=[[World War II]] |awards=[[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves]] }}
'''Helmut Kalbitz''' (3 January 1912 – 23 August 1944) was a highly decorated [[Major (Germany)|Major]] in the [[Wehrmacht]] during [[World War II]]. He was also a recipient of the [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves]]. The Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross and its higher grade Oak Leaves was awarded to recognize extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership.
==Awards and decorations== * [[Iron Cross]] (1939) ** 2nd Class (10 October 1939)<ref name="Scherzer p244">Scherzer 2010, p. 244.</ref><ref name="Thomas p343">Thomas 1997, p. 343.</ref> ** 1st Class (10 June 1940)<ref name="Scherzer p244"/><ref name="Thomas p343"/> * [[Wound Badge]] (1939) ** in Black (1 March 1940)<ref name="Scherzer p244"/> ** in Silver (7 October 1943)<ref name="Scherzer p244"/> ** in Gold (28 December 1943)<ref name="Scherzer p244"/> * [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves]] ** Knight's Cross on 7 September 1943 as ''[[Oberleutnant]]'' and chief of the 1./Pionier-Bataillon 125<ref name="Scherzer p429">Scherzer 2007, p. 429.</ref><ref>Fellgiebel 2000, p. 249.</ref> ** 366th Oak Leaves on 7 January 1944 as ''[[Hauptmann]]'' and commander of Pionier-Bataillon 31<ref name="Scherzer p429"/><ref>Fellgiebel 2000, p. 76.</ref>
